line_1: CA'NDISH, farewell! may Fame our names entwine!
line_2: Through life I lov'd thee, dying I am thine;

line_1: Her fairest olive wreath entwine;
line_2: And Hope, fond charmer, still be thine!

line_1: And all their odorous wings entwine;
line_2: Attendant cherubs sweetly join,

line_1: In grateful bondage did their limbs entwine,
line_2: With woodbine sweet, and twisted eglantine.

line_1: And willows and woodbines entwine;
line_2: Fond Zephyr caresses the pine;

line_1: And olive wreaths thy victor-brows entwine.
line_2: May fame and honour crown thy bold design,

line_1: Ye writhing adders, round my feet entwine;
line_2: Ye blasting meteors, upon me shine.

line_1: With Plato's olive wreath the bays entwine:
line_2: Those who in study, shou'd in practice shine.

line_1: 'The vine should round the elm entwine.
line_2: 'While still at friendship's sacred shrine,

line_1: Let reason, not riot, the garland entwine —
line_2: And now, my gay comrades, the myrtle and vine

line_1: See what gay flowers thy bust entwine!
line_2: See where I've deck'd thy once lov'd shrine

line_1: And the trees, which the woodbines entwine,
line_2: 'Tis true that the meadows are fine,

line_1: Immortal laurels to entwine,
line_2: Virtue with Genius must combine;

line_1: The wreath of pleasure gaily to entwine?
line_2: May not she strive around her sacred shrine

line_1: There love's soft blandishments entwine
line_2: Round every human heart but mine;

line_1: Which twisted briar or hasle-bands entwine;
line_2: From trampling cattle, and the routing swine.

line_1: Who preside o'er this Urn and it's myrtles entwine,
line_2: No, rather assist me, ye muses benign,

line_1: So shall my hands for thee the wreath entwine,
line_2: And strew fresh poppies at thy votive shrine.

line_1: OH, thou! who sleep'st where hazle bands entwine
line_2: I would, sweet maid! thy humble bed were mine,

line_1: And its gay branches to entwine,
line_2: Luxuriant wound the curling vine.

line_1: Oh goddess! now for me entwine
line_2: Of friendship at whose hallowed shrine,
